MANUAL INSTALL
==============

GTK Theme
----------
Use apt-get to install gtk-theme and icons
    https://github.com/snwh/paper-gtk-theme
Use Unity Tweak Tool to set theme and icons

Terminal Theme
---------------
cd ~/.config/base16-gnome-terminal/ && git clone https://github.com/chriskempson/base16-gnome-terminal
source .config/base16-gnome-terminal/base16-google.dark.sh

Shortcut Managment
------------------
Use apt-get to install 'CompizConfi Settings Manager'
Open and navigate to 'Ubuntu Unity Plugin' to view 'General', 'Launchers', 'Switchers', etc menus

Other keyboard shortcuts set at 'System Settings' > 'Keyboard' > 'Shortcuts':
    i.e. - gnome-session-quit --power-off --force -> <Ctrl><Alt><Del>

Vim Airline Fonts
-----------------
Use powerline pre-patched fonts by:
    git clone https://github.com/powerline/fonts
    Edit install.sh to put all fonts in ~/.fonts instead of ~/.local/share/fonts
    ./install.sh
    refresh font cache
    close all instances of terminal!
Else look at patching own font
